# First, build openSSL:
cd ~/tmp
wget http://www.openssl.org/source/openssl-0.9.7d.tar.gz
tar xzf openssl-0.9.7d.tar.gz
cd openssl-0.9.7d
./config
make
make test
sudo make install

cd ~/tmp
wget ftp://carroll.cac.psu.edu/pub/OpenBSD/OpenSSH/portable/openssh-3.8p1.tar.gz
tar xzf openssh-3.8p1.tar.gz
cd openssh-3.8p1
./configure
make
sudo make install


After all this, I could log in, but I couldn't seem to run xterm or other X
applications.  So I gave up and renamed /usr/local/bin/ssh* to
/usr/local/bin/openssh-ssh* .
